snippet.textDisplay:
In review of the Skikorsky medium weight helicopter accident at Burbank Airfield, it is observedd the aircraft should have been on an Instrument Flight Rule approach procedure. The Helicopter, a Skikorsky S Series has a maximum passenger rating of 13 people. 9 persons were reported aboard, which means it might have been at or near its maximum rated weight capacity. No word of carry aboards, or weights. The Skikorsky S Series medium weight helicopter, has a maximum speed of near 200 m.p.h. Near mountain areas are notorious also for an aerographical element referred to as ' canyon winds' Canyon winds occur near large hills, valleys, and mountainous areas, where ground level winds increase in speed, due to the rise of the ground terrain. REFERENCE :N.W.S. NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE, FAA PILOT REPORTING.
If the Skikorsky Helicopter was indeed at or near its maximum weight capacity, and an incident of gusts to canyon winds occurred, it could have caused an incident if light turbulence unrecoverable to control, if at or near ground obstructions.
We strongly suggest that the names of the accident victims NOT be released to public for Privacy of the Immediate Surviving Families.

The Skikorsky S Series is a 13 million dollar helicopter, and has been manufactured and in service since 1977.

Our Prayers to Kobe Bryant, a Dad, a Husband, a Professional Athlete, and an Olympian.
